    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A process in which a print, usually a photograph, is permanently adhered to a clear sheet of acrylic. This enhances the perception of color and sharpness, due to the acrylic's refractive qualities.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
